  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Blessing for the Crown Prince
  author: Monk Muui
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Lotus Sutra is the teaching honored by our Buddha, and so it must be revered before all else. The Crown Prince is the flesh and blood of our King, and so he deserves our devotion no less than the King himself. Thus we proclaim this truth with greater fervor, and offer our blessings with utmost sincerity.

    I am but a humble disciple, lacking virtue to benefit the world and wisdom to teach others. Yet in this twilight of my years, I have been graced with good fortune—to dwell in this prosperous age and to witness the worthy Crown Prince. For the sake of preserving the kingdom of Samhan, he journeyed far to the Dragon Court, and there received the boundless grace of the Son of Heaven. Now he returns to the Crane Ridge, and hearing this glorious news, I spread the sacred offerings and pour forth my deepest devotion, beseeching divine compassion.

    When we speak of the Buddha's attainment—the distant origin completed long ago—his lifespan knows no end. When we expound the wondrous principle of skillful means, widely opening the paths of salvation, all worldly forms abide eternally. Through this humble offering, as small as dust, I pray for the illumination of the bright mirror.

    May the light of compassion shine radiant across the realm. May the waters of grace grow clear and still. May his years of life be as long as the tortoise and the crane, and may his lineage endure unbroken forever. May the gentle wind of benevolence convert all distant lands, and may he eternally carry forward the glorious deeds of his ancestors.
  footnotes:
    - 'Samhan (三韓) refers to the three kingdoms of ancient Korea: Goguryeo, Baekje, and Silla.'
    - The Dragon Court (龍庭) is a poetic reference to the Chinese imperial court.
    - Crane Ridge (鵠嶺) refers to the Korean peninsula, traditionally symbolized by cranes and turtles.
    - This is a commemorative blessing written upon the Crown Prince's return from a diplomatic mission to China.
